.TH SHELL 1 "22/12/2024" "1.0" "Simple_Shell"

.SH NAME
shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shell
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shell
is a command interpreter that provides a user interface to execute commands. It reads commands from standard input or a file and executes them.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -c cmd
Executes the specified command
.TP
.B -r
Restricted mode
.TP
.B -i
Interactive mode
.TP
.B -v
Verbose mode

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B cd
Changes the current directory
.TP
.B pwd
Displays the current directory
.TP
.B echo
Displays text
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell with return code n

.SH USAGE
To start the shell, run:
.EX
$ ./shell
.EE

.SH EXAMPLES
Here are some examples of using the shell:
.EX
$ pwd
/home/user
$ echo "Hello World"
Hello World
$ exit
.EE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
The user's home directory
.TP
.B PATH
List of directories to search for commands

.SH AUTHORS
yassine and esteban

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
